        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 6 at 6:25PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Caseyville, or 11 miles west of Brookhaven, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Brookhaven, Vaughn, and Loyd Star around 630 PM CDT.
West Lincoln around 635 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
